===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Pinyin''' also '''[[pinyin]]'''<!--Collins only gives upper, M-W only gives lower, Encarta gives both but puts upper first-->

# A system of [[romanization]] (phonetic notation and transliteration to roman script) for Chinese based on the [[Mandarin]] dialect of the Beijing area used in the [[People's Republic of China]]. 

====Usage notes====
Although pinyin helps with pronouncing Chinese characters, one should be aware of the limits of its use as a pronunciation system. It mostly uses letters of the basic Roman alphabet, but some of these do not represent the sound that might normally be expected by an English reader.  Other than to express tonality, the only letter with diacritics that is used is "'''ü'''". It uses 4 different diacritics on vowels to represent tones: '''ā, á, ǎ, à''', but these are often replaced but the superscrpts '''<super>1 2 3 4</super>''' respectively when the diacritics cannot easily be represented.

